INSERT INTO exhibition VALUES ('2020-01-12 12:00:00','2019-10-08 12:00:00','','Édouard Manet was the Impressionist generation’s great painter of modern Paris. Considered \"deeply affecting\" by LA Times, this major show explores the last years of Manet’s short life and career, revealing his growing fascination with fashion, flowers, and fleeting beauty.','5defd31fe8bf700011c7f06a','Manet and Modern Beauty',NULL,'5139fa9d03a8b33748000004',3);
INSERT INTO exhibition VALUES ('2020-01-19 12:00:00','2019-10-15 12:00:00','','Early 20th-century American artists provide diverse perspectives on the shifting world around them. With works drawn from local museums and a private collection, True Grit provides a survey of printmaking from this period with a selection of photos from the Getty\'s collection.','5defeabdbb2aa200114f7707','True Grit: American Prints and Photographs from 1900 to 1950',NULL,'5139fa9d03a8b33748000004',3);
INSERT INTO exhibition VALUES ('2020-03-29 12:00:00','2019-12-03 12:00:00','','A selection of works on paper from the Getty Research Institute—including rare preparatory drawings, working proofs, and trial prints— shed light on Käthe Kollwitz’s creative process and reveal the depth of her social and political engagement.','5df13c1489b0e70012807c79','Käthe Kollwitz: Prints, Process, Politics',NULL,'5139fa9d03a8b33748000004',3);
INSERT INTO exhibition VALUES ('2020-05-09 12:00:00','2020-02-09 12:00:00','https://d32dm0rphc51dk.cloudfront.net/M0f90DVVR_Vq6F4ObUI6oA/medium.jpg','The first major solo exhibition at the Museum of the photographer’s incisive work in over 50 years. The exhibition includes approximately 100 photographs drawn entirely from the Museum’s collection. ','5e45bd6c89331c0011204383','Dorothea Lange: Words & Pictures',NULL,'54e766e67261696dd0810800',3);
INSERT INTO exhibition VALUES ('2020-06-14 12:00:00','2020-01-31 12:00:00','','Bea Nettles explores the narrative potential of photography through constructed images often made with alternative photographic processes. The first large-scale retrospective demonstrates this celebrated artist’s experimental approaches to art-making.','5e6298ed0e6b3a00118f21b2','Bea Nettles: Harvest of Memory',NULL,'50d32632112cf5a389000422',3);
